#: ../../source/install.rst:29
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are various ways to install BurnBox for Linux, but the recommended "
"way is to use either the `Flatpak <https://flatpak.org/>`_ or the `Snap "
"<https://snapcraft.io/>`_ package. Flatpak and Snapcraft ensure that you'll "
"always use the newest version and run BurnBox inside of a sandbox."
msgstr ""
"бһҳбһ¶бһ“бһңбһ·бһ’бһёбһҮбһ¶бһ…бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһ“бһҖбҹ’бһ“бһ»бһ„бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ BurnBox бһҹбһҳбҹ’бһҡбһ¶бһ”бҹӢ Linux бһ”бҹүбһ»бһ“бҹ’бһҸбҹӮбһңбһ·бһ’бһёбһҸбҹ’бһҡбһјбһңбһ”бһ¶бһ“бһҺбҹӮбһ“бһ¶бҹҶбһӮбһәбһҸбҹ’бһҡбһјбһңбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһҖбһүбҹ’бһ…бһ”бҹӢ "
"`Flatpak <https://flatpak.org/>`_ бһ¬бһҖбһүбҹ’бһ…бһ”бҹӢ `Snap <https://snapcraft.io/>`_ бҹ” "
"Flatpak бһ“бһ·бһ„ Snap бһ’бһ¶бһ“бһ¶бһҗбһ¶бһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһ“бһ№бһ„бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһҖбҹҶбһҺбҹӮбһҗбҹ’бһҳбһёбһ”бҹҶбһ•бһ»бһҸбһҮбһ¶бһ“бһ·бһ…бҹ’бһ… бһ бһҫбһҷбһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡбһҖбһ¶бһҡ BurnBox бһ“бҹ…бһҒбһ¶бһ„бһҖбҹ’бһ“бһ»бһ„ "
"sandboxбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:32
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Snapcraft support is built-in to Ubuntu and Fedora comes with Flatpak "
"support, but which you use is up to you. Both work in all Linux "
"distributions."
msgstr ""
"бһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҡбһ”бһҹбҹӢ Snap бһҸбҹ’бһҡбһјбһңбһ”бһ¶бһ“бһ—бҹ’бһҮбһ¶бһ”бҹӢбһҳбһҖбһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷ Ubuntu бһ бһҫбһҷ Fedora бһҠбҹӮбһӣбһ—бҹ’бһҮбһ¶бһ”бҹӢбһҳбһҖбһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҡбһ”бһҹбҹӢ "
"Flatpak бһ”бҹүбһ»бһ“бҹ’бһҸбҹӮбһўбҹ’бһңбһёбһҠбҹӮбһӣбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһӮбһәбһўбһ¶бһҹбҹ’бһҡбҹҗбһҷбһӣбһҫбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбҹ” бһ§бһ”бһҖбһҡбһҺбҹҚбһ‘бһ¶бҹҶбһ„бһ–бһёбһҡбһ“бҹҒбҹҮбһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһ“бҹ…бһҖбҹ’бһ“бһ»бһ„бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһ–бҹҗбһ“бҹ’бһ’вҖӢбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҸбһ·бһ”бһҸбҹ’бһҸбһ·бһҖбһ¶бһҡ "
"Linux бһ‘бһ¶бҹҶбһ„бһўбһҹбҹӢбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Install BurnBox using Flatpak**: https://flathub.org/apps/details/org."
"burnbox.BurnBox"
msgstr ""
"** бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ BurnBox бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫ Flatpak**бҹ– https://flathub.org/apps/details/org."
"burnbox.BurnBox"

#: ../../source/install.rst:36
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Install BurnBox using Snapcraft**: https://snapcraft.io/burnbox"
msgstr "** бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ BurnBox бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫ Snap **бҹ– https://snapcraft.io/burnbox"

#: ../../source/install.rst:38
msgid ""
"You can also download and install PGP-signed ``.flatpak`` or ``.snap`` "
"packages from https://burnbox.hideaway.chat/dist/ if you prefer."
msgstr ""
"бһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһҖбҹҸбһўбһ¶бһ…бһ‘бһ¶бһүбһҷбһҖ бһ“бһ·бһ„бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„бһҖбһүбҹ’бһ…бһ”бҹӢ ``.flatpak`` бһ¬ ``.snap`` PGP-signed бһ–бһё https://"
"burnbox.hideaway.chat/dist/ бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҹбһ·бһ“бһ”бһҫбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһ…бһ„бҹӢбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:41
#, fuzzy
msgid "Manual Flatpak Installation"
msgstr "бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„"

#: ../../source/install.rst:43
msgid ""
"If you'd like to install BurnBox manually with Flatpak using the PGP-"
"signed `single-file bundle <https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/single-file-"
"bundles.html>`_, you can do so like this:"
msgstr ""
"бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҹбһ·бһ“бһ”бһҫбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһҳбһ¶бһ“бһ”бҹҶбһҺбһ„бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ BurnBox бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһҒбҹ’бһӣбһҪбһ“бһҜбһ„бһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһ“бһ№бһ„ Flatpak бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһ¶бһҹбҹӢ GP-signed "
"`single-file bundle <https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/single-file-bundles."
"html>`_, бһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһўбһ¶бһ…бһ’бҹ’бһңбһҫбһҸбһ¶бһҳбһҠбһјбһ…бһ“бҹҒбҹҮбһ”бһ¶бһ“:"

#: ../../source/install.rst:45
msgid ""
"Install Flatpak by following the instructions at https://flatpak.org/setup/."
msgstr "бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ Flatpak бһҸбһ¶бһҳбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҺбҹӮбһ“бһ¶бҹҶбһ“бҹҒбҹҮ https://flatpak.org/setup/."

#: ../../source/install.rst:46
msgid ""
"Add the Flathub repository by running ``flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists "
"flathub https://flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo``. Even though you "
"won't be downloading BurnBox from Flathub, BurnBox depends on some "
"packages that are only available there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:47
msgid ""
"Go to https://burnbox.hideaway.chat/dist/, choose the latest version of BurnBox, "
"and download the ``.flatpak`` and ``.flatpak.asc`` files."
msgstr ""
"бһ‘бҹ…бһҖбһ¶бһ“бҹӢ https://burnbox.hideaway.chat/dist/ бһҠбһҫбһҳбҹ’бһ”бһёбһ’бҹ’бһңбһҫбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҮбҹ’бһҡбһҫбһҹбһҡбһҫбһҹбһ“бһјбһңбһҖбҹҶбһҺбҹӮбһ”бҹ’бһҡбҹӮбһ…бһ»бһ„бһҖбҹ’бһҡбҹ„бһҷбһ”бһ„бҹ’бһўбһҹбҹӢбһҡбһ”бһҹбҹӢ "
"BurnBox бһ“бһ·бһ„бһ‘бһ¶бһүбһҷбһҖ ``.flatpak`` бһ“бһ·бһ„ ``.flatpak.asc`` бҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:48
msgid ""
"Verify the PGP signature of the ``.flatpak`` file. See :ref:`verifying_sigs` "
"for more info."
msgstr ""
"бһ’бҹ’бһңбһҫбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһ”бһүбҹ’бһҮбһ¶бһҖбҹӢбһ бһҸбҹ’бһҗбһӣбҹҒбһҒбһ¶бһ“бҹғ PGP  ``.flatpak`` бҹ” бһҹбһјбһҳбһҳбһҫбһӣ :ref:`verifying_sigs` "
"бһҹбһҳбҹ’бһҡбһ¶бһ”бҹӢбһ–бҹҗбһҸбҹҢбһҳбһ¶бһ“бһ”бһ“бҹ’бһҗбҹӮбһҳбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:49
msgid ""
"Install the ``.flatpak`` file by running ``flatpak install BurnBox-"
"VERSION.flatpak``. Replace ``VERSION`` with the version number of the file "
"you downloaded."
msgstr ""
"бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ ``.flatpak`` бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡбһҒбҹҶбһҳбһ¶бһ“ ``flatpak install BurnBox-VERSION.flatpak`` "
"бҹ”  бһҮбҹҶбһ“бһҪбһҹ ``VERSION`` бһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһ“бһ№бһ„бһ…бҹҶбһ“бһҪбһ“бһҖбҹҶбһҺбҹӮбһ”бҹ’бһҡбҹӮбһӣбһҫбһҜбһҖбһҹбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹӮбһӣбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһ”бһ¶бһ“бһ‘бһ¶бһүбһҷбһҖбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:51
msgid "You can run BurnBox with: `flatpak run chat.hideaway.burnbox`."
msgstr ""
"бһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһўбһ¶бһ…бһ”бһҫбһҖбһҠбҹҶбһҺбһҫбһҡ BurnBox бһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһ“бһ№бһ„бһҒбҹҶбһҳбһ¶бһ“бҹ– `flatpak run chat.hideaway.burnbox`."

#: ../../source/install.rst:54
msgid "Manual Snapcraft Installation"
msgstr "бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ Snapcraft бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһҒбҹ’бһӣбһҪбһ“бһҜбһ„"

#: ../../source/install.rst:56
msgid ""
"If you'd like to install BurnBox manually with Snapcraft using the PGP-"
"signed Snapcraft package, you can do so like this:"
msgstr ""
"бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҹбһ·бһ“бһ”бһҫбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһ–бһ»бҹҶбһ…бһ„бҹӢбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„бһҖбһҳбҹ’бһҳбһңбһ·бһ’бһё BurnBox бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһ•бҹ’бһ‘бһ¶бһӣбҹӢбһҒбҹ’бһӣбһҪбһ“бһҮбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһ“бһ№бһ„ Snapcraft бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫбһҖбһүбҹ’бһ…бһ”бҹӢ PGP-"
"signed Snapcraft бһ“бҹ„бҹҮбһ‘бҹҒ бһ“бҹ„бҹҮбһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһўбһ¶бһ…бһ’бҹ’бһңбһҫбһҠбһјбһ…бһ“бҹҒбҹҮбһ”бһ¶бһ“бҹ–"

#: ../../source/install.rst:58
msgid ""
"Install Snapcraft by following the instructions at https://snapcraft.io/docs/"
"installing-snapd."
msgstr ""
"бһ’бҹ’бһңбһҫбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ Snapcraft бһҸбһ¶бһҳбһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҺбҹӮбһ“бһ¶бҹҶбһ“бҹ… https://snapcraft.io/docs/installing-snapd"

#: ../../source/install.rst:59
msgid ""
"Go to https://burnbox.hideaway.chat/dist/, choose the latest version of BurnBox, "
"and download the ``.snap`` and ``.snap.asc`` files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:60
msgid ""
"Verify the PGP signature of the ``.snap`` file. See :ref:`verifying_sigs` "
"for more info."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:61
msgid ""
"Install the ``.snap`` file by running ``snap install --dangerous "
"burnbox_VERSION_amd64.snap``. Replace ``VERSION`` with the version number "
"of the file you downloaded. Note that you must use `--dangerous` because the "
"package is not signed by the Snapcraft store, however you did verify its PGP "
"signature, so you know it's legitimate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:63
msgid "You can run BurnBox with: `snap run burnbox`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:68
msgid "Command-line only"
msgstr "бһҹбһҳбҹ’бһҡбһ¶бһ”бҹӢбһҸбҹӮ Command-line бһ”бҹүбһ»бһҺбҹ’бһҺбҹ„бҹҮ"

#: ../../source/install.rst:70
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can install just the command-line version of BurnBox on any operating "
"system using the Python package manager ``pip``. :ref:`cli` has more info."
msgstr ""
"бһўбҹ’бһ“бһҖбһўбһ¶бһ…бһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„бһҖбҹҶбһҺбҹӮ command line бһҡбһ”бһҹбҹӢ BurnBox бһ“бҹ…бһӣбһҫбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһ–бҹҗбһ“бҹ’бһ’бһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҸбһ·бһ”бһҸбҹ’бһҸбһ·бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҺбһ¶бһҳбһҪбһҷбһҠбҹ„бһҷбһ”бҹ’бһҡбһҫ "
"Python package manager ``pip``бҹ” бһҹбһјбһҳбһҳбһҫбһӣ:ref:`cli` бһҹбһҳбҹ’бһҡбһ¶бһ”бҹӢбһ–бҹҗбһҸбҹҢбһҳбһ¶бһ“бһ”бһ“бҹ’бһҗбҹӮбһҳбҹ”"

#: ../../source/install.rst:75
msgid "FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:77
msgid ""
"Althought not being officially developed for this platform, BurnBox can "
"also be installed on `FreeBSD <https://freebsd.org/>`_. It's available via "
"its ports collection or as pre-built package. Should you opt to install and "
"use BurnBox on a FreeBSD operating system, please be aware that it's "
"**NOT** officially supported by the BurnBox project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:79
msgid ""
"Though not being offered and officially maintained by the BurnBox "
"developers, the FreeBSD packages and ports do fetch and verifies the source "
"codes from the official BurnBox repository (or its official release "
"packages from `PyPI <https://pypi.org/project/burnbox-cli/>`_). Should "
"you wish to check changes related to this platform, please refer to the "
"following resources:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:81
msgid "https://cgit.freebsd.org/ports/log/www/burnbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:82
msgid "https://www.freshports.org/www/burnbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:85
#, fuzzy
msgid "Manual pkg Installation"
msgstr "бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„"

#: ../../source/install.rst:87
msgid ""
"To install the binary package, use ``pkg install pyXY-burnbox``, with "
"``pyXY`` specifying the version of Python the package was built for. So, in "
"order to install BurnBox for Python 3.9, use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:91
msgid ""
"There's also a **Command-line only** version of BurnBox available as pre-"
"built package. Replace ``py39-burnbox`` by ``py39-burnbox-cli`` if you "
"want to install that version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:93
msgid ""
"For additional information and details about the FreeBSD pre-built packages, "
"please refer to its `official Handbook section about pkg <https://docs."
"freebsd.org/en/books/handbook/ports/#pkgng-intro>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install.rst:96
#, fuzzy
msgid "Manual port Installation"
msgstr "бһҖбһ¶бһҡбһҠбҹҶбһЎбһҫбһ„ Snapcraft бһҠбҹ„бһҷбһҒбҹ’бһӣбһҪбһ“бһҜбһ„"

